cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper deals with people detection and tracking using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of Convolutional Neural Nets and Conditional Random Fields also suggests that the paper may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The focus on tracking multiple targets across multiple cameras suggests that the paper may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep learning techniques for multi-camera multi-target detection suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
